.TH HCC2D_ENCODER 1 "June 2026" "HCC2D CLI Encoder 0.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hcc2d_encoder \- encode text or file payloads as QR, HCC2D4, or HCC2D8 PNG images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hcc2d_encoder
[\fIoptions\fR]
\fIoutput.png\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBhcc2d_encoder\fR is a standalone command-line encoder for generating raster
PNG images containing standard QR symbols or HCC2D symbols.
It accepts either inline text or file bytes as input and can encode them
directly or wrap them in an HCC2DF container with filename metadata and
optional compression.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-text\fR \fISTRING\fR
Encode the UTF-8 bytes of \fISTRING\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-input-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Read raw bytes from \fIPATH\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-file-format\fR \fBhcc2df\fR|\fBraw\fR
Select payload framing.
\fBhcc2df\fR wraps the payload in an HCC2DF container and is the default.
\fBraw\fR encodes the bytes directly with no wrapper.
.TP
\fB\-\-mode\fR \fBqr\fR|\fBhcc2d4\fR|\fBhcc2d8\fR
Select the symbol family.
\fBqr\fR generates a standard black/white QR Code.
\fBhcc2d4\fR and \fBhcc2d8\fR generate 4-colour and 8-colour HCC2D symbols.
The default is \fBhcc2d4\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-ec-level\fR \fBL\fR|\fBM\fR|\fBQ\fR|\fBH\fR
Set the error-correction level.
The default is \fBQ\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
Set the symbol version from 1 to 40, or use 0 to auto-select the smallest
fitting version.
The default is 0.
.TP
\fB\-\-scale\fR \fIPX\fR
Set pixels per module in the output PNG.
The minimum is 6 and the default is 12.
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet-zone\fR \fIN\fR
Set the white border around the symbol in modules.
The default is 4.
.TP
\fB\-\-palette\fR \fBmodel1\fR|\fBmodel2\fR
Select the HCC2D colour palette.
Ignored for \fB\-\-mode qr\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Show the built-in help text and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Encode raw text as a standard QR symbol:
.B hcc2d_encoder \-\-text "https://hcc2d.com/spec" \-\-mode qr \-\-file-format raw qr.png
.TP
Encode a file as an HCC2DF-wrapped HCC2D8 symbol:
.B hcc2d_encoder \-\-input-file report.pdf \-\-mode hcc2d8 \-\-file-format hcc2df report.png
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B hcc2d_encoder
returns 0 on success and a non-zero status on failure.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/hcc2d_encoder
Installed command-line encoder.
